29:19.257 --> 29:21.927
It's not a question
about Los Angeles.

29:21.927 --> 29:23.995
It's a question about

29:23.995 --> 29:26.131
what you might be trying
to go toward

29:26.131 --> 29:28.433
- and why.
- Clean slate.

29:29.768 --> 29:31.136
A fresh start.

29:31.136 --> 29:33.271
Less conceptual, more specific.

29:33.271 --> 29:34.973
I am going toward

29:34.973 --> 29:37.142
a job.

29:37.142 --> 29:39.477
Something that I'm good at,

29:39.477 --> 29:42.914
you know,
but on a bigger scale and-and

29:42.914 --> 29:46.017
there's just more opportunity,
there's more need.

29:46.017 --> 29:48.253
Plus, a new set of colleagues

29:48.253 --> 29:50.822
you don't have any
uncomfortable history with,

29:50.822 --> 29:52.724
too, right?

29:55.694 --> 29:58.597
You're kind of
all over the place today.

29:58.597 --> 30:00.565
It's fine, but I just--
I don't know, I thought

30:00.565 --> 30:02.300
I should point it out in case
you're not doing it on purpose.

30:02.300 --> 30:05.670
I just want to make sure
this very big move

30:05.670 --> 30:07.339
has a goal,

30:07.339 --> 30:10.275
besides running away
from your father.

30:10.275 --> 30:12.243
Because you know that saying,

30:12.243 --> 30:14.779
"Wherever you go,
there you are."

30:15.847 --> 30:19.417
<i>He said you'd been gone
