30:43.842 --> 30:46.411
<i>what do you think you're gonna
do when you need something?</i>

30:46.411 --> 30:48.346
<i>Because you are gonna
need something, honey.</i>

30:48.346 --> 30:51.683
<i>You're a fucking
black hole of need.</i>

31:04.200 --> 31:06.236
<i>I'm diving into
all this stuff again.</i>

31:06.236 --> 31:08.171
<i>It's taking me
right back to college,</i>

31:08.171 --> 31:10.674
<i>finding a copy of</i> Man And His
Symbols <i>in the used bookstore.</i>

31:10.674 --> 31:12.475
<i>I feel like I should be
wearing a rugby shirt</i>

31:12.475 --> 31:13.910
<i>and drinking Snapple.</i>

31:13.910 --> 31:15.545
Anyway,

31:15.545 --> 31:17.180
<i>there is some stuff
about the Toni Wolff affair</i>

31:17.180 --> 31:18.648
<i>in the Hannah memoir.</i>

31:18.648 --> 31:20.050
<i>About how the three of them
were able</i>

31:20.050 --> 31:21.384
<i>to coexist through it,</i>

31:21.384 --> 31:23.286
<i>with Jung's wife
being fully aware</i>

31:23.286 --> 31:25.855
<i>and Toni being aware
she was aware.</i>

31:46.609 --> 31:48.211
<i>STELLA Skater buddy Ellen.</i>

31:48.211 --> 31:50.313
Hey. What you up to?

31:50.313 --> 31:52.816
<i>Um... just got home
from Pilates,</i>

31:52.816 --> 31:55.852
<i>which means
I'm about to order tacos.</i>

31:55.852 --> 31:57.954
<i>You want in?</i>

31:57.954 --> 32:00.757
- Be right over.
<i>- Cool.</i>

32:06.396 --> 32:08.998
<i>I wanted you to have this.</i>

32:08.998 --> 32:10.667
What is it?

32:10.667 --> 32:12.402
It's my paperwork

32:12.402 --> 32:14.437
that I need to submit
to a judge for a new trial.

32:14.437 --> 32:17.440
Why I deserve one.
Alternative suspects,

32:17.440 --> 32:19.876
people who weren't
looked at the time.

32:19.876 --> 32:22.412
- Like who?
- Well, like a guy she dated,

32:22.412 --> 32:23.947
a guy who lived in the building,

32:23.947 --> 32:26.683
people who were identified
by fingerprints

32:26.683 --> 32:29.419
who hadn't been arrested
at the time, things like that.

32:30.420 --> 32:32.388
Now that it's ready,
we're gonna do it.

32:32.388 --> 32:34.724
We're gonna submit it.

32:37.227 --> 32:39.863
And I-I wanted you to have it.

32:39.863 --> 32:41.297
Obviously,
you don't have to read it.

32:41.297 --> 32:42.999
No, I want to read it.

32:42.999 --> 32:45.001
Okay.

32:45.001 --> 32:46.836
That's great.

32:48.004 --> 32:49.572
It just seems like...

32:51.674 --> 32:53.543
...like there's-there's so...

32:53.543 --> 32:55.712
much of it. I mean, I...

32:55.712 --> 32:57.514
I get about the fingerprints,

32:57.514 --> 32:59.749
but did they not even, like...

32:59.749 --> 33:01.651
try to find out
any of this stuff then?

33:01.651 --> 33:03.853
Why wouldn't they look
at other people in her life?

33:03.853 --> 33:05.722
Because I lied.

33:09.726 --> 33:11.261
I lied.

33:11.261 --> 33:14.564
And I made it easy for them.

33:14.564 --> 33:17.066
But I hope this makes...

33:17.066 --> 33:20.036
anything...

33:20.036 --> 33:22.806
easier for you.

33:28.711 --> 33:31.948
It was clear to me that he was
coming from her apartment.

33:31.948 --> 33:35.451
But you didn't actually
see him leave it.

33:35.451 --> 33:37.654
Ms. Rauch,
when was the last time

33:37.654 --> 33:39.422
you had your vision checked?

33:39.422 --> 33:40.623
Can you recall?

33:40.623 --> 33:43.159
This year, last year?

33:43.159 --> 33:45.295
Probably around...

33:45.295 --> 33:46.563
three years ago?

33:46.563 --> 33:48.231
Did you ever see my client

33:48.231 --> 33:51.801
inside Ms. Forrest's apartment?

33:53.203 --> 33:54.537
No.

33:54.537 --> 33:57.874
Did you ever see my client
with Ms. Forrest?

33:57.874 --> 33:59.843
No.

34:00.610 --> 34:04.180
Get out! Nothing. We're nothing.

34:04.180 --> 34:06.082
We are nothing.

34:07.383 --> 34:10.653
<i>♪ Three times again ♪</i>

34:10.653 --> 34:14.023
<i>♪ She cries your name... ♪</i>

34:27.737 --> 34:30.073
<i>"Torment" is the word.</i>

34:32.842 --> 34:35.712
<i>So afraid of being wrong,</i>

34:35.712 --> 34:38.982
<i>people judging her,
leaving her.</i>

34:38.982 --> 34:40.650
<i>It's okay, Maria.</i>

34:40.650 --> 34:41.851
<i>You expect people
to care about you</i>

34:41.851 --> 34:43.319
<i>when you treat them like this?</i>

34:43.319 --> 34:44.921
<i>And it's hopeless.</i>

34:44.921 --> 34:46.689
<i>What do you think
you're gonna do</i>

34:46.689 --> 34:48.658
<i>when you need something?
Because you are gonna</i>

34:48.658 --> 34:50.293
<i>need something, honey.
"Torment" is the word.</i>

34:50.293 --> 34:51.928
<i>You're a fucking
black hole of need.</i>

34:51.928 --> 34:53.329
<i>You expect people
to care about you</i>

34:53.329 --> 34:54.597
<i>when you treat them like this?</i>

34:54.597 --> 34:56.599
<i>And it's hopeless.</i>

35:53.056 --> 35:55.191
<i>Hello.</i>

35:55.191 --> 35:57.493
<i>No one is available
to take your call.</i>

35:57.493 --> 36:00.363
<i>Please leave a message af...</i>

36:05.468 --> 36:07.170
<i>Who is this?</i>

36:09.205 --> 36:11.574
It's me, Dad.

36:11.574 --> 36:13.543
<i>Of course it is.</i>

36:13.543 --> 36:15.712
<i>Why would you care
if you woke me up?</i>

36:15.712 --> 36:18.081
Sorry. Um...

36:20.283 --> 36:22.051
...how are you?

36:22.051 --> 36:24.520
<i>How am I?</i>

36:24.520 --> 36:27.623
<i>Well, when was the last time
we talked?</i>

36:27.623 --> 36:30.927
<i>When did you go AWOL
out of nowhere, again?</i>

36:30.927 --> 36:32.762
September.

36:32.762 --> 36:35.064
<i>Really? Seven months?</i>

36:35.064 --> 36:38.201
<i>Didn't feel like that long.
You sure?</i>

36:40.470 --> 36:42.472
Yeah, I'm sure.

36:43.339 --> 36:45.708
<i>Well, since you're calling
all this attention</i>

36:45.708 --> 36:48.745
<i>to how long it's been,
how did you want me to be?</i>

36:48.745 --> 36:51.981
<i>Or were you thinking
about me at all?</i>

36:53.816 --> 36:55.752
<i>I mean,
is there an upward trajectory?</i>

36:55.752 --> 36:57.854
<i>You keep talking
about this Conchita</i>

36:57.854 --> 37:00.056
<i>who runs the show there.
How did you get that job?</i>

37:00.056 --> 37:03.192
<i>Or maybe you'd rather
just be told what to do forever.</i>

37:03.192 --> 37:05.728
<i>That's what it seems like, honestly.</i>

37:06.529 --> 37:09.132
- Is it an apology?
<i>- No. For what?</i>

37:09.132 --> 37:11.567
<i>I don't know.
For the things that you said,</i>

37:11.567 --> 37:13.536
<i>for the way that you said them.</i>

37:13.536 --> 37:15.071
<i>Okay, wait.</i>

37:15.071 --> 37:17.774
<i>Which time
that you overreacted was this?</i>

37:17.774 --> 37:19.776
<i>Okay, then,
how about you apologize</i>

37:19.776 --> 37:22.478
<i>for how
you fucking ruin everything?</i>

37:22.478 --> 37:24.047
<i>What are we ruining again?</i>

37:24.047 --> 37:26.349
<i>What... what is there to ruin?
Seriously...</i>

37:26.349 --> 37:29.152
<i>...tell me, Alex,
because I... I don't know.</i>

37:29.152 --> 37:31.788
<i>He's your age,
but he's not married?</i>

37:31.788 --> 37:33.389
<i>Is he divorced?</i>

37:33.389 --> 37:35.758
No.

37:38.694 --> 37:40.363
<i>Well, that's just weird.</i>

37:40.363 --> 37:41.998
<i>You don't think that's weird?</i>

37:41.998 --> 37:43.533
No, I don't think that's weird.

37:43.533 --> 37:45.101
I think that he's really busy.

37:45.101 --> 37:48.137
Like, he's busy being head
of Major Crimes Bureau.

37:48.137 --> 37:50.440
He's so busy,
they offered him a judgeship,

37:50.440 --> 37:52.642
and he had to turn it down.

37:52.642 --> 37:54.410
<i>I think
something's wrong with him.</i>

37:54.410 --> 37:56.779
There must be, right,

37:56.779 --> 37:59.115
because he's interested in me?

37:59.916 --> 38:01.818
<i>Is that what I said?</i>

38:01.818 --> 38:03.820
<i>But you probably don't have</i>

38:03.820 --> 38:05.221
<i>to worry about it, anyway,</i>

38:05.221 --> 38:07.123
<i>because it doesn't sound
like he is.</i>

38:07.123 --> 38:08.958
Okay.

38:08.958 --> 38:11.227
So you still think
that there's nothing to ruin?

38:11.227 --> 38:14.197
<i>Well, he's a lawyer.
You say he's a good one.</i>

38:14.197 --> 38:16.032
<i>I'm not a lawyer,
but even I know--</i>

38:16.032 --> 38:18.201
<i>you leave a door open,
someone's gonna come in.</i>

38:18.201 --> 38:19.936
Right, so I should
just call him.

38:19.936 --> 38:22.138
Shit.

38:22.138 --> 38:24.874
<i>Maybe you're a little bit jealous.</i>

38:24.874 --> 38:26.909
<i>Of what?</i>

38:26.909 --> 38:28.945
That I finally found somebody

38:28.945 --> 38:32.682
who loves me
and who wants to be with me.

38:32.682 --> 38:34.383
<i>Why would I be jealous?</i>

38:34.383 --> 38:36.319
<i>I'm happy for you.</i>

38:36.319 --> 38:38.554
<i>You make me sound like
some kind of monster.</i>

38:40.123 --> 38:42.558
<i>Just manage your expectations,
that's all.</i>

38:42.558 --> 38:45.695
<i>It's bad to go into something
already thinking it's forever.</i>

38:45.695 --> 38:48.664
<i>Just let it be
what it's going to be.</i>

38:48.664 --> 38:50.233
<i>Why is it a jealous thing</i>

38:50.233 --> 38:52.068
<i>to remind you
to live in the moment?</i>

38:52.068 --> 38:55.004
<i>I'm just protecting you, honey.</i>

38:55.004 --> 38:57.473
<i>That's all
I'm ever trying to do.</i>

38:57.473 --> 38:59.575
And after she found out

38:59.575 --> 39:02.345
he was married,
what happened then?

39:02.345 --> 39:05.148
Well, she confronted him,
and he turned on her.

39:06.249 --> 39:08.050
He told her if she tried
to make any trouble for him,

39:08.050 --> 39:10.853
he'd start by making sure
she lost her job.

39:10.853 --> 39:13.923
And what did you think
at that point?

39:13.923 --> 39:15.925
I was devastated for her.

39:15.925 --> 39:18.995
And I was... worried.

39:18.995 --> 39:22.098
The way she was describing him,
he was a...

39:22.098 --> 39:23.933
a completely different person

39:23.933 --> 39:27.403
than the one I'd been
hearing about.

39:27.403 --> 39:29.405
Instead of a loving boyfriend, suddenly,

39:29.405 --> 39:34.277
there's this angry,
powerful guy, and...

39:34.277 --> 39:38.648
my daughter's not
his girlfriend now,

39:38.648 --> 39:41.350
she's his problem.

39:43.152 --> 39:45.388
And what happened next,
Mr. Forrest?

39:45.388 --> 39:47.690
She called me.

39:47.690 --> 39:50.793
She was hysterical.

39:50.793 --> 39:53.896
She said
she'd tried to talk to him.

39:54.931 --> 39:56.766
Then he got violent,

39:56.766 --> 39:59.168
put hands on her.

40:00.736 --> 40:03.172
She'd been scared for her life.

40:07.777 --> 40:10.613
I didn't know what to do.

40:10.613 --> 40:13.382
I felt so helpless.

40:13.382 --> 40:15.885
I just told her...
told her to get out of there,

40:15.885 --> 40:18.588
come home, I'd take care of her.

40:26.062 --> 40:28.864
And she said
she was going to, but before

40:28.864 --> 40:31.367
she could leave, he...

40:31.367 --> 40:33.803
You broke her,
and then you killed her!

40:33.803 --> 40:35.938
She was my best friend!

40:38.140 --> 40:40.376
Nothing further, Your Honor.

40:55.157 --> 40:59.028
I'm very sorry
for your loss, Mr. Forrest.

41:01.063 --> 41:03.466
One question.

41:05.801 --> 41:09.572
You have no actual evidence

41:09.572 --> 41:11.774
for this "relationship"

41:11.774 --> 41:14.043
between your daughter

41:14.043 --> 41:16.579
and Mr. Gallagher, do you?

41:19.849 --> 41:22.118
Yes, I do.

41:24.520 --> 41:26.589
And...

41:28.190 --> 41:30.960
...what would that be?

41:39.935 --> 41:41.671
There.

42:03.264 --> 42:05.299
Epic. I mean, holy shit.

42:05.299 --> 42:07.501
Come on. This is a page-turner.

42:07.501 --> 42:08.869
- Really?
- Yeah.

42:08.869 --> 42:10.338
I remember the one case.

42:10.338 --> 42:12.473
A restaurant, the son
beating the dad to death.

42:12.473 --> 42:13.808
Unbelievable.

42:13.808 --> 42:15.609
And the pill mill
across the hall?

42:15.609 --> 42:18.079
- Alex threatening the guy
in actual words?
- Yeah.

42:18.079 --> 42:19.947
That's what he's saying now.

42:19.947 --> 42:21.615
And how many cases,
historically, have we seen

42:21.615 --> 42:24.618
of people like him killing
people like her for less?

42:26.454 --> 42:28.656
I do have kind of a hard time
thinking of Gabriel Ibarra

42:28.656 --> 42:31.425
as a guy who'd solve
that problem that way, but...

42:31.425 --> 42:33.160
this is a trial application, right?

42:33.160 --> 42:34.829
You got to pull out
all the stops.

42:34.829 --> 42:37.698
But you can't expect me to be
that happy about it, though.

42:37.698 --> 42:40.768
I mean, I had you sewn up as one
of the greatest secret weapons

42:40.768 --> 42:42.770
any law firm could have.

42:42.770 --> 42:45.339
You working here was gonna
make me so look so good,

42:45.339 --> 42:47.375
I should have known
it couldn't last.

42:48.376 --> 42:50.444
Anyway...
Hey, I almost forgot

42:50.444 --> 42:52.413
the Ukrainian woman's husband
trying to beat Dan up,

42:52.413 --> 42:54.815
- thinking he was you.
- Yeah, yeah, and the best part

42:54.815 --> 42:56.684
about it is,
he violated his parole,

42:56.684 --> 42:59.687
so for the next five to ten,
we'll know where he is.

42:59.687 --> 43:01.756
Hey, do you put a full bakery
like this out every day,

43:01.756 --> 43:03.457
or just on Mondays?
You want to come do
some freelance

43:03.457 --> 43:05.126
investigating for us?
Hmm?

43:05.126 --> 43:07.128
Every day is muffin day here.

43:07.128 --> 43:09.597
And an omelet bar on Fridays.

43:09.597 --> 43:11.932
Shut your mouth.

43:13.267 --> 43:15.069
<i>when Marcella Leyva</i>

43:15.069 --> 43:17.071
was elected D.A., she asked me

43:17.071 --> 43:19.340
to come over
as chief investigator.

43:19.340 --> 43:24.145
Dan was already being promoted
as head of Major Crimes.

43:24.145 --> 43:25.880
And he said
he'd put in a word for me.

43:25.880 --> 43:28.849
And did
your professional relationship

43:28.849 --> 43:33.087
with Mr. Gallagher change
as a result of these promotions?

43:33.087 --> 43:35.089
Um, we made a good team.

43:35.089 --> 43:38.192
And it deepened our friendship.

43:38.192 --> 43:41.328
Can you tell us,
over your career,

43:41.328 --> 43:44.765
how many homicide investigations
have you conducted

43:44.765 --> 43:46.600
or supervised?

43:46.600 --> 43:50.337
- Uh, hundreds.
- And that vast experience

43:50.337 --> 43:52.440
must have helped you
develop a sense

43:52.440 --> 43:56.076
for whether someone is capable
of that crime.

43:56.877 --> 43:58.312
I believe it has, yes.

43:58.312 --> 44:00.714
So, putting aside
your friendship,

44:00.714 --> 44:04.018
can you give us
your professional opinion

44:04.018 --> 44:07.154
as to whether Dan Gallagher...

44:08.722 --> 44:10.825
...could commit

44:10.825 --> 44:13.160
murder?

44:14.962 --> 44:16.864
Never.

44:16.864 --> 44:18.966
He couldn't do it. It's just...

44:18.966 --> 44:20.935
It's not in the guy.

44:20.935 --> 44:23.037
<i>You said you were concerned</i>

44:23.037 --> 44:27.141
that the victim was
delusional and dangerous.

44:27.141 --> 44:29.743
Did you report those concerns

44:29.743 --> 44:31.412
to Human Resources?

44:31.412 --> 44:33.314
I didn't want
to escalate the situation...

44:33.314 --> 44:35.416
It's a "yes or no" question.

44:36.383 --> 44:37.852
No.

44:37.852 --> 44:39.787
Did you report the situation

44:39.787 --> 44:44.725
to the district attorney,
or to the victim's supervisor,

44:44.725 --> 44:46.427
- Ms. Lewis?
- No.

44:46.427 --> 44:48.128
Did you contact the LAPD

44:48.128 --> 44:50.130
to report this delusional

44:50.130 --> 44:52.500
and dangerous woman?

44:52.500 --> 44:54.034
No, I did not.

44:54.034 --> 44:56.270
Thank you, Detective.

45:07.581 --> 45:10.017
Detective,
is it true that you went

45:10.017 --> 45:11.752
to Ms. Forrest's
apartment building

45:11.752 --> 45:14.421
on the day of her murder?

45:15.256 --> 45:17.591
- I...
- Yes or no, please.

45:26.066 --> 45:27.601
Yes.

45:27.601 --> 45:29.937
That's all, Detective.
Thank you.

45:36.677 --> 45:38.946
<i>I got her address
from the employee roster,</i>

45:38.946 --> 45:41.115
and I went there
to speak with her.

45:41.115 --> 45:45.252
I thought maybe if we spoke
someplace that she felt safe,

45:45.252 --> 45:47.254
she would hear me
when I told her

45:47.254 --> 45:48.722
that I am a family man,

45:48.722 --> 45:51.892
that I would never
reciprocate her feelings.

45:51.892 --> 45:55.396
And I wanted to avoid
a public spectacle for her sake.

45:56.463 --> 45:59.934
In retrospect,
I know that was naive.

46:02.303 --> 46:04.638
I don't think I realized
how far gone she was.

46:06.941 --> 46:09.209
Until she kidnapped my daughter.

46:10.744 --> 46:13.213
So that's why
they recovered your fingerprints

46:13.213 --> 46:15.616
inside Alex's apartment?

46:16.784 --> 46:18.218
Yes, it is.

46:19.486 --> 46:22.256
Well, why did you tell
Detective Brooker

46:22.256 --> 46:24.558
you didn't know where she lived?

46:26.360 --> 46:28.629
Uh, he's mistaken.
I didn't say that.

46:34.835 --> 46:36.937
Dan...

46:36.937 --> 46:41.275
did you kill Alexandra Forrest?

46:42.910 --> 46:44.979
No, I did not.

46:48.015 --> 46:50.084
I have spent my entire life

46:50.084 --> 46:51.919
in the service of justice.

46:51.919 --> 46:55.456
It would go against
everything that I believe

46:55.456 --> 46:57.791
to take someone else's.

46:58.959 --> 47:01.395
No matter how afraid I was,
I just couldn't do that.

47:02.363 --> 47:04.365
Not to Alexandra Forrest,
not to anyone else.

47:04.365 --> 47:06.200
<i>Mr. Gallagher, when</i>

47:06.200 --> 47:09.336
you realized your daughter had
been kidnapped by Alex Forrest,

47:09.336 --> 47:11.972
did you call the police?

47:11.972 --> 47:14.274
- No.
- The FBI?

47:16.443 --> 47:18.445
I was preparing
to call the FBI.

47:18.445 --> 47:22.016
So, faced with every parent's
greatest nightmare,

47:22.016 --> 47:25.352
you had to prepare
to call the FBI.

47:25.352 --> 47:27.621
Did you ever call them?

47:30.357 --> 47:32.259
- No.
- Did you already

47:32.259 --> 47:35.696
know when you came up
with the kidnapping story

47:35.696 --> 47:38.932
that you were going
to murder her?

47:38.932 --> 47:40.868
<i>I wa-- I di-- No.</i>

47:40.868 --> 47:43.470
<i>You used her, and then
you tried to throw her away.</i>

47:43.470 --> 47:45.105
I didn't. I...

47:45.105 --> 47:46.840
<i>And when she wouldn't go,</i>

47:46.840 --> 47:49.309
you threatened her,
you physically assaulted her,

47:49.309 --> 47:50.577
<i>and you killed her.</i>

47:50.577 --> 47:52.079
<i>She's ready</i>

47:52.079 --> 47:54.448
to say good night.

47:59.620 --> 48:01.221
You should know
that you can say "no"

48:01.221 --> 48:03.657
to what I'm about to ask you.

48:05.259 --> 48:09.396
But you should also know that,
after how today went...

48:09.396 --> 48:11.932
...I'm probably gonna need you
to say "yes."

48:14.668 --> 48:18.272
Mm, she just said
she was a friend of my dad's,

48:18.272 --> 48:21.308
and that he needed me
to go with her.

48:21.308 --> 48:24.545
I asked her things,
and she knew it all--

48:24.545 --> 48:26.613
my dad's name,
my mom's name,

48:26.613 --> 48:30.884
their jobs,
and even my dog's name, so...

48:30.884 --> 48:35.055
Hmm, okay,
and where'd you two go?

48:36.390 --> 48:38.625
Just to a park,
and we walked around.

48:38.625 --> 48:40.394
Hmm.

48:40.394 --> 48:43.030
I'm going to show you a book.

48:43.030 --> 48:45.132
Okay?

48:48.202 --> 48:49.870
Do you recognize it?

48:49.870 --> 48:52.306
Yeah, it's mine.

48:52.306 --> 48:55.609
<i>The Story Of Layla
and Majnun.</i>

48:55.609 --> 48:57.845
This book was found
inside the apartment

48:57.845 --> 48:59.813
of the woman
you went to the park with.

48:59.813 --> 49:02.649
- Do you know how she got it?
- I gave it to her.

49:02.649 --> 49:04.651
Can I have it back, please?

49:04.651 --> 49:07.421
Of course.
As soon as the trial is over.

49:07.421 --> 49:09.590
Is this a picture of the woman

49:09.590 --> 49:11.825
who took you to the park?

49:11.825 --> 49:13.494
Yeah, that's her.

49:13.494 --> 49:15.195
For the record, the photo

49:15.195 --> 49:18.098
is of Alexandra Forrest.
Nothing further.

49:18.098 --> 49:20.067
Thank you.

49:21.668 --> 49:22.836
Ms. Ruiz?

49:22.836 --> 49:24.571
No questions, Your Honor.

49:24.571 --> 49:26.707
Okay, then. Thank you, Ellen.

49:26.707 --> 49:28.842
Thank you.

49:49.163 --> 49:51.198
All rise.

50:03.110 --> 50:06.113
I'll remind you all
we're here today because

50:06.113 --> 50:09.683
an innocent woman named
Alexandra Forrest was murdered,

50:09.683 --> 50:12.286
and because
a jury found Mr. Gallagher

50:12.286 --> 50:14.621
guilty of this terrible crime.

50:15.722 --> 50:17.724
I read your application.

50:17.724 --> 50:21.428
Not only was it well-written
and considered,

50:21.428 --> 50:24.531
it raises
very compelling questions.

50:24.531 --> 50:28.068
But the salient,
relevant argument to be made

50:28.068 --> 50:29.837
is that you are a liar.

50:29.837 --> 50:33.173
You lied
to the investigating detective,

50:33.173 --> 50:34.908
Earl Brooker.

50:34.908 --> 50:37.444
You lied under oath
at your trial.

50:37.444 --> 50:39.813
You lied
at your parole hearing.

50:39.813 --> 50:42.649
So I don't think
it's unfair to presume

50:42.649 --> 50:44.818
you've probably lied

50:44.818 --> 50:47.287
in this application
before the court.

50:47.287 --> 50:50.991
As a result, it's impossible
to know, as I sit here today,

50:50.991 --> 50:54.995
which version of your story
I'm supposed to believe.

50:54.995 --> 50:57.831
In this court,
the truth is important.

50:57.831 --> 51:00.634
And the truth
in this court today is

51:00.634 --> 51:04.238
that you have received
more than enough attention

51:04.238 --> 51:06.273
and indulgence

51:06.273 --> 51:08.709
on this case already.

51:08.709 --> 51:11.778
Simply stated,
the criminal justice system

51:11.778 --> 51:14.781
has given you all the justice
you deserve.

51:14.781 --> 51:17.517
So I'm not going
to give you any more.

51:17.517 --> 51:20.721
I'm denying your motion
for a new trial.

51:20.721 --> 51:23.557
Please give the defendant
written notice

51:23.557 --> 51:25.926
of his right to appeal.

51:33.567 --> 51:35.168
<i>As to the charge of murder,</i>

51:35.168 --> 51:38.372
how do you find the defendant,
Daniel Gallagher?

51:38.372 --> 51:40.674
Guilty.

52:18.245 --> 52:21.181
- ...have the time.
- The library, right?

52:21.181 --> 52:22.749
Okay.

52:22.749 --> 52:25.886
Oh, hey. Hi.
You have a Stella, uh, Chapman

52:25.886 --> 52:28.188
- in your Research Methods
section, right?
- Mm-hmm.

52:28.188 --> 52:30.557
Well, when's the last time
you talked to her?

52:30.557 --> 52:32.592
I... don't know.

52:32.592 --> 52:34.027
- Huh.
- How come?

52:34.027 --> 52:35.929
Well, I mean, she hasn't
showed up to work study

52:35.929 --> 52:37.464
since Tuesday,
and Dr. Ranum said

52:37.464 --> 52:39.099
he didn't see her
in morning seminar.

52:39.099 --> 52:40.701
And she's not answering
her texts,

52:40.701 --> 52:42.402
and her voice mailbox is full.

52:42.402 --> 52:44.404
Wow. I...

52:44.404 --> 52:47.007
- I-I wish I could help.
- Okay.

52:47.007 --> 52:49.142
Okay.

52:49.977 --> 52:52.245
Yeah, that'd be great.

52:53.814 --> 52:55.949
I kept finding reasons
not to go to the office

52:55.949 --> 52:57.751
till Arthur finally pointed out

52:57.751 --> 53:01.221
that I hadn't been there
in person in an actual year.

53:01.221 --> 53:04.524
So, we, uh...

53:04.524 --> 53:06.526
wiggled out of the lease

53:06.526 --> 53:09.730
and just started working
from here.

53:09.730 --> 53:11.732
I can see why.

53:11.732 --> 53:13.133
Yeah, it's crazy.

53:13.133 --> 53:15.235
Sometimes
I can't believe I live here.

53:24.578 --> 53:26.813
How are you doing?

53:30.550 --> 53:32.753
I had my hearing.

53:33.653 --> 53:36.656
I was able to stand
in front of a judge.

53:37.491 --> 53:40.427
And she denied my application.

53:40.427 --> 53:42.829
And what does that mean?

53:42.829 --> 53:45.432
I will not be getting
a new trial.

53:47.534 --> 53:49.770
But did she read
the application?

53:49.770 --> 53:52.005
There was so much
new information.

53:52.005 --> 53:55.075
Ellen and I...
How can they just...?

54:00.614 --> 54:02.883
I'm so sorry.

54:02.883 --> 54:05.152
I have wanted this for so long.

54:05.152 --> 54:07.587
Because even after
the way that I hurt you,

54:07.587 --> 54:09.856
you just always...

54:09.856 --> 54:12.692
believed in me.

54:13.727 --> 54:17.564
I wanted you to be able to know
that you'd been right to do it.

54:17.564 --> 54:22.135
Now, you will forever have
to just take that on faith.

54:28.675 --> 54:30.610
I don't need another trial

54:30.610 --> 54:33.180
to tell me what I already know.

54:36.950 --> 54:39.786
It's what my mom always said.

54:39.786 --> 54:42.823
Faith is knowing
without being shown.

54:54.067 --> 54:56.036
I need you to take Ellen.

54:56.036 --> 54:57.904
- Take her with you.
- Okay.

54:57.904 --> 55:00.907
- Where are you going?
- The house
on Satsuma's a shitshow.

55:00.907 --> 55:03.110
I've been leaving Arthur
to deal with all of it.

55:03.110 --> 55:05.245
I'll be back.
Just distract her.

55:05.245 --> 55:09.015
Don't say anything
about us to her, please.

55:10.350 --> 55:12.419
Of course. I wouldn't.

55:18.758 --> 55:20.760
The special.

55:24.731 --> 55:27.234
I'll have the same.

55:37.611 --> 55:39.412
Thank you for coming.

55:39.412 --> 55:41.148
Why wouldn't I?

55:41.148 --> 55:44.184
How else was I going
to find out what you want?

55:45.785 --> 55:48.855
